<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5>red as a beetroot • red as cherries</xh5><p> <i>red as a beetroot—</i>1. red in the face from feeling ashamed: If his friends talked about girls, he went as <u>red as a beetroot</u>. 2. sunburnt: After a day shooting around Sydney, they are as <u>red as a beetroot</u>! But if it was only the harsh sun that they had to counter, life would have been easy. </p><p><i>red as cherries—</i>1. said of rosy complexion (indicating good health): Today you see them [women] bouncing, <u>red as cherries</u>, and tomorrow they exhibit themselves effete as dead weeds.... 2. said of flushed cheeks: My little brother, cheeks as <u>red as cherries</u> and eyes all a-glow, comes bursting in the house after a long day of sledding. 3. said of fresh red lips: She had long, lustrous, Japanese eyes, very quick and alert, lips as <u>red as cherries</u> and the most beautiful teeth in the world.</p> </entry>
